I developed a solution similar to the one by @assylias. To circumvent the problematic with parallel stream @StuartMarks mentioned, I first make a given parallel stream sequential, perform the mapping and restore the parallel state.

`public static &lt;T&gt; Stream&lt;Tuple2&lt;Integer, T&gt;&gt; zipWithIndex(Stream&lt;T&gt; stream) {
	final AtomicInteger index = new AtomicInteger();
	final Function&lt;T, Tuple2&lt;Integer, T&gt;&gt; zipper = e -&gt; Tuples.of(index.getAndIncrement(), e);
	if (stream.isParallel()) {
		return stream.sequential().map(zipper).parallel();
	} else {
		return stream.map(zipper);
	}
}`

